# Phase 5 web dashboard (docs/phase-5-web-dashboard.md): web/ is the Vite
# frontend source, but its build output lands in internal/web/dist (see
# web/vite.config.ts's outDir — go:embed can't reach outside its own
# package directory). Only internal/web/dist/index.html is committed, as a
# placeholder so `go build ./...` works without Node on a fresh clone; the
# real build's hashed asset files are regenerated by `npm run build` (CI
# and deploy.yml both do this before the Go build step) and never committed.
web/node_modules/
web/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
internal/web/dist/assets/
